Poster for Peaceful Year Photo: Courtesy of Zhao XinChinese quju opera Peaceful Year will be staged at Beijing's Tianqiao Theater May 13-17, the Beijing Quju Theater announced during its open day on Tuesday. The opera follows the story of a group of people living in a small hutong before the founding of the People's Republic of China in 1949. According to the production's scriptwriter Wang Xinji, the story will examine the changes that occurred in people's lives after the liberation of Beijing. Wang said he sees the opera, which started with an idea 10 years ago, as a gift for this year's celebration of the 70th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Delegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los AngelesChinese driving Vegas growthHaving fun